# Expo Environment Variables
# ==========================
#
# LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (expo start):
#   Expo loads .env files in this order (highest priority first):
#   1. .env.development.local - Local overrides (gitignored)
#   2. .env.local             - Local overrides (gitignored)
#   3. .env.development       - Development defaults
#   4. .env                    - Base defaults
#
#   Create your local env:
#     cp .env.example .env.development
#
# EAS BUILDS:
#   EAS Build does NOT auto-load .env files!
#   Options for EAS builds:
#   1. Define env vars in eas.json per profile (see eas.json)
#   2. Use EAS Secrets: https://docs.expo.dev/eas/environment-variables/
#   3. Pull from EAS: eas env:pull --environment development
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_* vars are available via process.env in your code
#
# Pull Convex vars: pnpm env:pull:convex

# =============================================================================
# CONVEX (required)
# =============================================================================
# Get from: npx convex dev or https://dashboard.convex.dev
EXPO_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-project.convex.cloud

# =============================================================================
# EAS (optional, for CI)
# =============================================================================
# Get from: expo.dev account settings
# EXPO_TOKEN=
